Comment (src/composables/useDashboardSuggestions.ts:265):
**[Medium] The run poller halts permanently on a transient poll error.** `pollLatest`'s `catch { stop() }` clears the interval on *any* thrown error — including a transient network blip or 5xx while the run is still `pending`/`running`. Once stopped nothing restarts it: the progress bar freezes at its last value, the `onPoll` callback stops refreshing pending suggestions, and the failure is invisible (the poller's `error` ref isn't rendered anywhere). So a single flaky poll silently kills the headline 'generation progress' feature for the rest of the session.

Suggestion: only `stop()` on terminal/not-found conditions; for a transient error, leave the interval running (optionally with backoff) so polling resumes on the next tick. If you do choose to stop, surface the failure (toast or inline message) so the frozen UI is explained.
